cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.QI, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses a new constructive mode for private quantum encryption and proposes a quantum block encryption scheme. The paper also compares the proposed scheme with quantum one-time pad and discusses its security. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of pseudorandom functions and their security in constructing the proposed quantum block encryption scheme. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of the proposed scheme and how a $2n$-bit key can be used in an exponential number of encryptions. 
4. cs.QI (Quantum Physics) - The paper discusses the use of quantum mechanics in modern cryptography and proposes a quantum encryption scheme. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the implementation of the proposed quantum block encryption scheme and how it only requires the implementation of two kinds of single-qubit gates.
